# Python Virtual Environment

Project uses `uv` with `.venv` at repo root.

Rules:
- Never run bare `pip install`. Use `uv pip install ... --python .venv/bin/python`.
- Never run bare `python`. Use `.venv/bin/python` or `uv run python`.
- Add dependencies to `pyproject.toml` first.
- Verify: `.venv/bin/python -c "import <pkg>"`.